						               													<description>The objective of El Plan, t&amp;uacute; decides is to be the player with most innovate business ideas after twelve rounds (1 year).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the game there are:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     3 resources: money, energy, workforce&amp;#10;     3 processes: logistics, production and marketing &amp;#10;     3 goods: raw material, consumer goods and services&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every player will receive a business card that tells him which his strengths are. With his abilities he will be able to produce 2 of the 3 kinds of goods the game has. They produce these goods by using processes to transform resources into goods.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The boards has several places where you can get resources, have additional processes, buy and sell goods, buy cards (which give new abilities) and others.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;By the end of every year players can transform 3 good, 1 of each, into an innovate idea. This can happen as many times as they like, if they have the necessary goods. Also, innovate ideas can be used as a joker for money, energy or workforce during the game.&amp;#10;Since each player is able to produce only 2 of the 3 goods, they will be forced to buy the third one every time they want to create an innovate idea.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
